title: For Sale:  500 Rounds 9x18 Makarov Ammo - 94 Grain FMJ Bullet
postcontent:
10 boxes or 500 rounds total of Silver Bear brand 9x18 Makarov ammo. This ammo is made in Russia by Barnual and is similar to Wolf & Tula brands except that Silver Bear uses a zinc plating process on their cases rather than a sprayed/dipped lacquer. This gives them a brushed nickel appearance that I assume is intended to provide more resistance to corrosion and perhaps to aid in smooth clambering/ejection from your pistol? 

I used a fair amount of this before I sold my Russian MAK and it functioned reliably. It was clean burning leaving little residue. Plus it was just as accurate as any of the other ammo I tried - even the big name brand varieties. It was also $6 - $10 less per box than any of the American made stuff I could buy at the time. So it's a good value for the money.

Price for the 500 rounds is $150 picked up in the Brandon area. Must be at least 21 to purchase. Thanks for looking.
